# chaos.gob -- demonstrates GobbleScript's irrational ops: ~ ? @ $ %
# Run this one more than once -- it will not always print the same thing.
# (everything up through 'Gobble' is plain deterministic Brainfuck-style
#  code, just to prove it still works the normal way too.)

# --- deterministic part: "Hello, Gobble" ---
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++.>  # 'H' (72)
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++.>  # 'e' (101)
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++.>  # 'l' (108)
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++.>  # 'l' (108)
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++.>  # 'o' (111)
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++.>  # ',' (44)
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++.>  # ' ' (32)
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++.>  # 'G' (71)
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++.>  # 'o' (111)
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++.>  # 'b' (98)
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++.>  # 'b' (98)
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++.>  # 'l' (108)
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++.>  # 'e' (101)

# --- chaotic letter: BURP (~) jitters the cell by -5..+5 before printing,
#     so this lands on 'n' about a sixth of the time, and a nearby
#     letter (i..s) the rest -- same source, different output, every run.
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++~.>  # base 'n' (110) plus random noise

# --- HICCUP (?) before a newline: 50% chance the '.' right after it
#     gets skipped entirely, so the newline sometimes just... doesn't happen.
++++++++++?.>  # newline (10), maybe

# --- GOBBLE (@) eating its own troublemaker: '@' permanently deletes the
#     '~' that comes right after it, BEFORE it can fire. So 'N' prints
#     reliably every time, even though a burp instruction is sitting
#     right there in the source -- it just never gets the chance to run.
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++@~.>  # 'N' (78), chaos pre-emptively eaten

++++++++++.  # final newline, deterministic

# --- pure flourish, no visible effect: REFLUX (%) flips < and >,
#     BELCH ($) teleports the pointer -- but the program ends right after,
#     so nothing downstream ever sees the difference. They still 'happen'.
%$
